    kind: "listing",
    supplement: "Listing",
    caption: [The segment circuit, the proof of one $M$-node piece. It range-checks its nodes to guard the leaf-index arithmetic (a), binds the published sorted set to the nodes it actually visited (b), pins its endpoints (c), proves each of the $M-1$ internal edges against the committed root the same way @fig:flat-merkle did (d), and binds the published partial cost to their sum (e). Distinctness, coverage, and global range it leaves to the glue's coverage sort of @fig:hier-glue. The visit order #inline[cycle_segment] stays private; only the sorted set is published.],
    pseudocode-list(hooks: 0.5em, booktabs: true, booktabs-stroke: 1pt)[
      + *circuit* #fn[segment]$(N, M, DEPTH)$ #h(1fr)
        + *public* $sortednodes[rng(0, M-1)], med startnode, med endnode, med partialcost, med root$
        + *private* $cyclesegment[rng(0, M-1)], med edgecosts[rng(0, M-2)],$
        + #h(2.4em) $siblings[rng(0, (M-1) dot DEPTH - 1)], med pathbits[rng(0, (M-1) dot DEPTH - 1)]$ #h(1fr) #lc[hint: $M-1$ edge proofs]
